commit ff99b6cf966e67135a592e41a5218786dc83bf08
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 10:10:05 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(list-edit): ListItemId brand + list-item ids + read-path id-backfill
    
    Branch 2 sub-commit 2.1 of the registration-launch stack (ADR 0006).
    
    - Add the `ListItemId` brand (a nanoid, URL-safe 21-char alphabet) earned at
      the schema boundary, plus `newListItemId` to mint one.
    - Add the required `id: ListItemId` to the three list-item structs (`Speaker`,
      `Seminar`, `TeamMember`); ids are content (round-trip + persist), not derived.
    - Migrate the bundled defaults once: stable nanoids on the 2 speakers, 3
      seminars, and 3 team members.
    - Add the read-path id-backfill normalization (`id-backfill.ts`): a one-shot
      parse->backfill->decode repair so a `content/site.json` published before ids
      existed still decodes on read (the deploy-safety hazard). Idempotent; never
      mints over an existing id. Wired into both the public read path
      (`content.server.ts`) and the admin draft/published read path
      (`draft-editor.server.ts`).
    - Record the one-shot backfill in ADR 0006's consequences.
    - Tests: `ListItemId` validation + brand assertion; id-backfill decode-safety,
      idempotence, no-mint-over-existing, bad-id-rejected, non-object passthrough;
      a public-read deploy-safety integration test over an id-less bucket document.

